<TITLE> Workers Party demands debate on oil, gas deals </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 2 (bdnews24.com)--Bangladesh Workers' Party, a component of the ruling Grand Alliance, has demanded discussion in parliament and a public hearing at the standing committee on the energy ministry before the government signs deal with foreign companies on offshore oil and gas exploration. A meeting of the party on Friday termed the explanation of Petrobangla about Model PSC (production-sharing contract) 2008, passed during the caretaker government, as distorted and devoid of truth. According to the rules and clauses of PSC 2008, the ownership of gas extracted will be, in fact, in the hands of the foreign companies in the signed agreement, it said. Also, the meeting discussed the preparation of the eighth party congress in Dhaka on Nov 14-18. The meeting was presided over by president Rashed Khan Menon, MP. General secretary Bimol Biswas, Politburo member Abul Bashar and central committee member Mahmudur Rahman Manik, among others, were present
